  <introduction>
    <p>
      Explain why each of the following matrices fails to be in row echelon form.
    </p>
  </introduction>
<exercise>
  <statement>
    <p>
      <m>A=\begin{bmatrix}
      1 \amp 2\amp 2\amp -3\\
      0\amp -3\amp 4\amp 0\\
      0\amp 0\amp 0\amp 1
      \end{bmatrix}</m>
    </p>
  </statement>
  <solution>
    <p>
      The first nonzero term in the second row is not a one.
    </p>
  </solution>
